{"name": "colorscript", "metadata": {"name": "ColorScript", "version": "2024.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://colourscript-documentation.readthedocs.io/", "dependencies": [], "summary": "A package for functionality with text, escape codes, octal and hexadecimal codes, and other data.", "upload_time": 1735519292}, "documentation": ["![https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TariqTheCoder/ColourScript-Documentation/refs/heads/main/Screenshot%202024-11-22%20191301.png](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TariqTheCoder/ColourScript-Documentation/refs/heads/main/Screenshot%202024-11-22%20191301.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n[![Code style: black](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg)](https://github.com/psf/black)\r\n[![PyPI - Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/colourscript)](https://pypi.org/project/ColourScript/)\r\n[![PyPI Licence](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/colourscript.svg?v=1)](https://pypi.org/search/?c=License+%3A%3A+OSI+Approved+%3A%3A+MIT+License)\r\n[![Docs Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/colourscript-documentation/badge/?version=latest)](https://colourscript-documentation.readthedocs.io/en/latest/)\r\n# ColorScript Package\r\n\r\nThis is a simple yet effective package to manipulate ASCII and other codes in Python. \r\nMore functionality has been added in later versions: Data has been added in version 0.0.6 and above.\r\n- ASCII escape codes\r\n- RGB codes for functionality not found in native Python\r\n- Data\r\n- Characters and functionality for strings and output\r\n\r\n*This module is authored by Tariq Tayebi: 2024 Sydney, Australia, and is licensed under the MIT License*\r\n\r\n## How To Use\r\nColorScript is divided into two sections:\r\n- data, and\r\n- functions\r\n\r\nFunctions allow to manipulate text, while data has codes and other important data for manipulating text.\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\nYou can install ColorScript with pip:\r\n>pip install ColorScript\r\n\r\nor you can go to https://pypi.org/project/ColourScript and download the .whl file or tar.gz file on Linux and open it.\r\n\r\n**Note: You must have Python on your computer. You can install it at https://python.org**\r\n\r\n### Testing\r\nAfter you have installed it, you can import it into a Python file:\r\n>from ColorScript import functions as cs #for importing functions\r\n>\r\n> from ColourScript import data as cd #for importing data\r\n\r\nIf you want to import both, type:\r\n>from ColorScript import * as cs\r\n\r\nor\r\n>from ColourScript import functions,data as cs\r\n\r\nAfter the module has been imported, you can use it, for example:\r\n>cs.text.AliceBlue(\"Hello World\") #function\r\n> \r\n>x = cs.ANSI.codes.octal.COLOURS[\"GREEN\"] #data\r\n\r\n**Note that you have to explicitly type the colour you want the text to be, otherwise it will stay the same. For example if you type AliceBlue, all the text outputted in the future will be AliceBlue unless outputted as plain.**\r\n\r\nFor a complete documentation on how to use this module, go to:\r\nhttps://colourscript-documentation.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ColorScript", "documentation": ["import either the data or function section of this module:"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ColorScript.cs", "xref": {"fqname": "ColorScript.functions", "project": null}}, {"name": "ColorScript.data", "xref": {"fqname": "ColorScript.data", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ColorScript.data", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [{"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.codes", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [{"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.codes.octal", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.codes.octal.COLOURS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.codes.octal.FORMATS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.codes.rgb", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "documentation": []}, {"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.characters", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ColorScript.data.ANSI.characters.CHARACTERS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "ColorScript.functions", "documentation": ["This is the function section of the ColorScript module."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ColorScript.functions.text", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "ColorScript.functions.text.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ColorScript.functions.text.reset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This function is used to reset the text formatting.\n\nThis is in octal function\n:return:"]}, {"name": "ColorScript.functions.text.plain", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This function prints plain text. \n\nThis is an octal function\n\n:return:"]}, {"name": "ColorScript.functions.text.red", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This function prints red text.\nThis is an octal f